INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("243", "3", "2017-06-19 14:33:24", "2017-06-19 11:33:24", "<h2><strong>How to use this application step-by-step?</strong></h2>\r\nThe use of this application differs depending on the user’s role, which means there are different features for public authorities and for citizens.\r\n<h3><strong><em>A. For public authorities</em></strong></h3>\r\n<h4><strong><u>Step 1 - Setup a RIS3 Action Plan Co-Design Process</u></strong></h4>\r\nWhen accessing the initial page of the application, users willing to use the application for starting a RIS3 Action Plan Co-Design process should select the corresponding link in the left part of their screen.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_226\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"767\"]<img class=\"wp-image-226 \" src=\"http://actionplan.s3platform.eu/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/A1-300x151.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"767\" height=\"386\" /> Figure 1. Step 1 for using this ONLINE S3 application[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong> i. Create a new Action Plan: </strong>Using the menu on the left, the user has to select the <em>Add New </em>option under the Action Plan submenu.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_227\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"776\"]<img class=\"wp-image-227 \" src=\"http://actionplan.s3platform.eu/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/A2-300x150.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"776\" height=\"388\" /> Figure 2. Create a new Action Plan[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>ii.</strong> <strong>Enter Action Plan</strong><strong>’s </strong><strong>details: </strong>A title and a short description in your language and in English is mandatory in order to create an Action Plan.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_228\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"652\"]<img class=\"wp-image-228 \" src=\"http://actionplan.s3platform.eu/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/A3-300x227.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"652\" height=\"493\" /> Figure 3. Enter Action Plan’s details[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>iii. Define region and consultation process: </strong>A list with all the European regions and countries can be found on the right. At the bottom of the page, users can add information about the consultation status of the co-design process and its due date.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_229\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"612\"]<img class=\"wp-image-229 \" src=\"http://actionplan.s3platform.eu/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/A4-300x226.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"612\" height=\"461\" /> Figure 4. Define region and consultation process[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>iv. Publish the Action Plan: </strong>Before proceeding in adding Actions in the Action Plan, the user has to publish the new Action Plan using the <em>Publish </em>button on the right.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_230\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"574\"]<img class=\"wp-image-230 \" src=\"http://actionplan.s3platform.eu/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/A5-300x209.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"574\" height=\"400\" /> Figure 5. Publish the Action Plan[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>v. Add actions: </strong>At the bottom of the page, the user can add the actions corresponding to this Action Plan, entering its title in both the desired language and English. All actions created at this point are immediately associated with this Action Plan and adopt its properties, which means the name of the region and country assigned.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_231\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"659\"]<img class=\"wp-image-231 \" src=\"http://actionplan.s3platform.eu/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/A6-300x146.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"659\" height=\"321\" /> Figure 6. Add Actions to an Action Plan[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>vi.</strong> <strong>Edit an action: </strong>There are two different ways to add more information related to each action. The first is clicking on the <em>Edit </em>button at the bottom of the Action Plan page, and the second one is clicking on <em>All items </em>from the <em>Actions </em>menu in the left sidebar of the application.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_232\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"540\"]<img class=\"wp-image-232 \" src=\"http://actionplan.s3platform.eu/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/A7-300x185.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"540\" height=\"333\" /> Figure 7. Edit an Action[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>vii.</strong> <strong>Enter details about each action: </strong>To edit an action, the user has to fill in a template with all the necessary information related to it. In order to provide a good quality Action Plan, it is highly recommended that all the fields are adequately completed.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-234  aligncenter\" src=\"http://actionplan.s3platform.eu/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/A8_1-e1497871920147-300x256.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"453\" height=\"386\" />\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_235\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"479\"]<img class=\"wp-image-235 \" src=\"http://actionplan.s3platform.eu/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/A8_2-300x245.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"479\" height=\"391\" /> Figure 8 Template for an Action[/caption]\r\n<h4><strong><u>Step 2 - </u></strong><strong><u>Receive feedback from citizens</u></strong></h4>\r\nOnce the consultation period is over, public authorities have to collect citizens’ comments as well as rating results for each action of the Action Plan separately. This information is the feedback used as input of the following and last step of the application.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_236\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"577\"]<img class=\"wp-image-236 \" src=\"http://actionplan.s3platform.eu/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/A9-300x149.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"577\" height=\"287\" /> Figure 9 Step 2 for using this ONLINE S3 application[/caption]\r\n<h4><strong><u>Step 3 – </u></strong><strong><u>Update the Action Plan</u></strong></h4>\r\nConsidering both the comments and the overall rating submitted by the citizens, the Action Plan is updated in order to be better adapted to their needs and priorities.\r\n<h3><strong><em>B. For citizens</em></strong></h3>\r\nWhen accessing the initial page of the application, users willing to use the application for participating in a RIS3 Action Plan Co-Design process should select the corresponding link in the right part of their screen.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_237\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"630\"]<img class=\"wp-image-237 \" src=\"http://actionplan.s3platform.eu/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/B1-300x151.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"630\" height=\"317\" /> Figure 10 How citizens can use this ONLINE S3 application[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>i. Find an Action Plan for your region/country: </strong>Users are able to search for an Action Plan based on its name, the associated regions and/or its consultation status.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_238\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"625\"]<img class=\"wp-image-238 \" src=\"http://actionplan.s3platform.eu/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/B2-300x145.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"625\" height=\"302\" /> Figure 11 Find an Action Plan for your region/country.[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>ii. Choose an Action: </strong>Once an Action Plan is selected from the list, a new page appears, including a short description of the plan, its consultation status and a list of actions associated to it. Clicking on each one of the actions on the right, more details about it will appear.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_239\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"669\"]<img class=\"wp-image-239 \" src=\"http://actionplan.s3platform.eu/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/B3-300x127.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"669\" height=\"283\" /> Figure 12 Choose an Action from a specific Action Plan[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>iii. Comment and rate an action: </strong>At the bottom of the Action’s page, users can find some short and predetermined questions regarding the completeness, maturity, popularity and other characteristics. These questions are answered using a 5-star rating scale and a comment field is also available. The participation process is completed by publishing a comment.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_240\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"670\"]<img class=\"wp-image-240 \" src=\"http://actionplan.s3platform.eu/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/B4-300x185.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"670\" height=\"413\" /> Figure 13 Comment and rate an Action[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;", "User\'s Guide", "", "inherit", "closed", "closed", "", "103-revision-v1", "", "", "2017-06-19 14:33:24", "2017-06-19 11:33:24", "", "103", "http://actionplan.s3platform.eu/2017/06/19/103-revision-v1/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
